Examples
OptionColumns
The dialog system supports helper tags you can put between square brackets.
What tag would you like to see an example of?
prompt
Adding a [color=Gold]\[prompt\][/color] tag adds a prompt[8] after[9] every[10] word.
page

Even though this is a single dialog line, when it hits a [color=Gold]\[page\][/color] tag...
[12]...it'll scroll the current line to a new page to read the rest!
goto
The name of this section is "Examples". [color=Gold]\[goto Examples\][/color] will return you to the beginning of the section. Let's go!
speed
This text will be read at regular speed.
[16]This will be read at half speed because of the tag [color=Gold]\[speed=0.5\][/color].
[18]And this will be read at double speed due to a tag of [color=Gold]\[speed=2\][/color]!
pause
You can can pause the script for a set amount of time using the "pause" tag.
We've added [color=Gold]\[pause=2\][/color] here[21] so it stops then continues on!
auto
If you add an [color=Gold]\[auto\][/color] tag to the end of a line, it will automatically proceed after a pause based on the length of the text being written.
You can also set a specific amount of time to pause in seconds.
This line ends with [color=Gold]\[auto=2\][/color].[25]
You can also set an auto tag on its own line. This will make all lines auto-proceed until you turn it off.
We added an auto tag right before this line so this will automatically proceed.
This will also auto-proceed.
[color=Gold]\[/auto\][/color] closes the tag, so you'll need to proceed manually from here!
end
[color=Gold]\[end\][/color] ends the script. Goodbye!
